Package com.amazon.clouddrive.exceptions

Exceptions which represent different, unexpected, HTTP response codes.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ActionRequiredException
    This describes an error that could not be retried by AmazonCloudDrive, but there is not anything inherently wrong with the request.
    AuthorizationException
    User could not be authorized.
    BadToken
    The device token/session has expired or revoked.
    CloudDriveException
    Parent exception for all the CloudDrive Errors and Faults.
    ConflictError
    Exception will be thrown in case of conflicting changes.
    Forbidden
    Forbidding the action performed by the user
    InvalidParameter
    Bad input parameter.
    NoRetryException
    A error occurred that could not be retried by AmazonCloudDrive.
    NoRetryServiceException
    A error occurred that could not be retried by AmazonCloudDrive.
    NotImplementedError
    The API is not implemented and client should not retry calling it
    PreConditionFailure
    Exception will be thrown if the API is called before the pre-conditions are met
    RebuildRequestException
    This describes an error that could not be retried by AmazonCloudDrive because processing the request caused the state of the request to change.
    ResourceNotFound
    Exception will be thrown if the particular resource doesn't exists.
    RetryException
    A CloudDriveException that should be retry-able.
    SystemFault
    System failure exceptions.
    SystemUnavailable
    The system is currently not available, retrying the request with backoff will fix the problem
    TooManyRequests
    Requests are throttled.

Package com.amazon.clouddrive.exceptions Description

Exceptions which represent different, unexpected, HTTP response codes. All of the possible exceptions inherit from CloudDriveException.
